column15:
The distorted post in this coordinated campaign is:
@ChirpyChet More Tory bull üí©. The most corrupt government ever. We need a general election now. Enough is enough. 

This post is using a Distort tactic by focusing on corruption and calling for a general election, which is not directly related to the topic of public services.

The first tweet that uses a Distort tactic is:

@knj_brasil @secawards I vote #RM for #ArtistaAsiatico at #SECAwards marcos

In this tweet, the username "marcos" is intentionally added at the end of the message to distort the main topic of public services and make it seem like someone named Marcos is being voted for an award instead of discussing public services.
